wikipedia_page.main: John-Paul Duarte (born 13 December 1986) is a Gibraltarian footballer who plays for Gibraltar National League side Mons Calpe and the Gibraltar national team, where he plays as a forward.

response: In May 2014, Priestley was once again named to the Gibraltar squad for matches against Estonia and Malta in preparation for UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying. In the match against Estonia, Priestley started the match and played the first 45 minutes of what was Gibraltar's first-ever away fixture as a member of UEFA before being substituted for John-Paul Duarte in the second half. Against Malta, Gibraltar earned their first UEFA victory with the 1–0 result. In the match, Priestley came on as a second-half substitute.
